2.	Scenario and Initial Data 
The hospital stores patient records in a doubly circular linked list. Each patient node contains patientID, name, severity, arrivalOrder, next pointer, and prev pointer. Severity 10 means most critical. If two patients have the same severity, the patient with lower arrivalOrder gets priority. 
Node 	Patient ID 	Name 	Severity 	Arrival 	Circular Links 
P1 	101 	Ali 	4 	1 	P7 <-> P1 <-> P2 
P2 	102 	Sara 	9 	2 	P1 <-> P2 <-> P3 
P3 	103 	Usman 	4 	3 	P2 <-> P3 <-> P4 
P4 	104 	Hina 	7 	4 	P3 <-> P4 <-> P5 
P5 	105 	Bilal 	2 	5 	P4 <-> P5 <-> P6 
P6 	106 	Zara 	9 	6 	P5 <-> P6 <-> P7 
P7 	107 	Hamza 	5 	7 	P6 <-> P7 <-> P1 
 
